- "shining stars" refers to players who are among the top 3 scorers;
- "constellation of the top 3 teams" refers to the top 3 teams by goals scored;
- "both the players and their teams have scored the most goals" means that the players are among the top 3 scorers and their teams are among the top 3 scoring teams.

- The "grand arena of competition" refers to the league where teams compete;
- "stands atop the podium" means the team with the highest rank;
- "basking in the glory of the highest total points" means the team with the most points.

- "crown jewels of the football world" refers to the top-performing teams in their respective leagues;
- "leading their leagues" means the teams are in the first position;
- "goal statistics" include total goals scored, total goals conceded, and goal difference.

- A high performer is defined as a player who has scored more than 10 goals and assists combined;
- The query filters out players who have not contributed to any goals or assists;
- The results are ordered by the player's name.
